{{Orphan|date=September 2017}}
The '''murder of Francesca Bimpson''' occurred on 2 December 2008 in the [[Everton, Liverpool|Everton]] district of [[Liverpool]]. Shortly after midnight, the Bimpson family's home was set on fire in what investigators determined to be [[arson]]. Francesca's mother, father, brother, and two sisters were able to escape from the burning home, but three-year-old Francesca was trapped in a bedroom and later rescued by [[firefighter]]s. She died in a hospital on 23 December.<ref name=Echo20090107>{{cite news|last=Traynor|first=Luke|title=Francesca Bimpson: Her final terrifying moments|url=http://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/liverpool-news/local-news/2009/01/07/francesca-bimpson-her-final-terrifying-moments-100252-22628967/|accessdate=13 February 2012|newspaper=Liverpool Echo|date=7 January 2009}}</ref>
Authorities later arrested Graham Heaps in conjunction with the arson, alleging that the arson was an act of retaliation against the family after Francesca's aunt ended a romantic relationship with him between 4–5 months earlier.<ref name=LDP20091208>{{cite news|last=Griffiths|first=Chloe|title=Arsonist Graham Heaps convicted of murdering Liverpool 3-year-old Francesca Bimpson |url=http://www.liverpooldailypost.co.uk/liverpool-news/regional-news/2009/12/08/arsonist-graham-heaps-convicted-of-murdering-liverpool-3-year-old-francesca-bimpson-92534-25342836/2/|accessdate=2012-02-13|newspaper=Liverpool Daily Post|date=8 December 2009}}</ref> On 7 December 2009 Heaps was [[conviction|convicted]] of Francesca Bimpson's murder and [[Sentence (law)|sentenced]] to [[life imprisonment]]. He will be eligible for parole after serving 28 years.
