'''Vedius Aquila''' was a military commander of ancient Rome who lived in the 1st century CE. He commanded the [[Roman legion|thirteenth legion]], and was one of [[Otho]]'s generals during the [[Year of the Four Emperors]]. He was present in the [[Battle of Bedriacum#First Battle of Bedriacum|First Battle of Bedriacum]], in which Otho's troops were defeated by those of [[Vitellius]], in 70.

After Otho's suicide, Vedius Aquila subsequently espoused [[Vespasian]]'s party.<ref>[[Tacitus]], ''[[Histories (Tacitus)|Histories]]'' 2.44, 3.7</ref>

